[1] CDC & WHO Press Briefings on EVD
Date: 2 Sep 2014
Source: AFluDiary [edited]
http://afludiary.blogspot.co.uk/2014/09/cdc-who-press-briefings-on-ebola.html


Today [2 Sep 2014], the World Health Organization and the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention [CDC] both held press conferences (unfortunately, at the same time) on the Ebola virus disease outbreak in West Africa. Both carried similar messages.

The EVD outbreak in West Africa is moving faster than the response currently being mounted against it. A concerted international effort is needed now to defeat this epidemic, with the implied threat that we either deal with it now in Africa, or we risk having to deal with it for years to come around the globe.

CDC director Dr Thomas Frieden painted a grim picture in his update on the Ebola outbreak in West Africa, saying that the epidemic was "spiraling out of control", but stressed there was still a "small window of opportunity" to contain it.

A transcript and audio file should be posted on the CDC Media website, hopefully later today [2 Sep 2014], with links to videos of the WHO/UN briefing.
http://www.cdc.gov/vhf/ebola/index.html?s_cid=cdc_homepage_feature_001

