[3] Liberia: new US doctor case, nurses strike

2 Sep 2014: (ABC News Radio) Another American doctor working for the missionary group SIM [Serving in Mission] has tested positive for Ebola in Liberia. The doctor was treating pregnant women at ELWA [Eternal Love Winning Africa] Hospital in Monrovia, Liberia, according to SIM. But he was not treating EVD patients in the hospital's separate EVD isolation facility, the group said, adding that it was unclear how he contracted the virus. ...
http://abcnewsradioonline.com/health-news/another-american-doctor-tests-positive-for-ebola-in-west-afr.html#ixzz3CBli2TQz


Liberia: nurses strike
----------------------
2 Sep 2014: (Reuters/AFP) Nurses on strike at Monrovia hospital are demanding protective equipment which they say has not been provided. [They are] demanding higher salaries as well as protective equipment against EVD. At the John F. Kennedy hospital in Monrovia, the nurses sought personal protective equipment, hazmat-style suits that protect against the spread of the disease, reports AFP.
http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/ebola-liberia-nurses-strike-demanding-higher-pay-protective-gear-1463545

