[4] Prevention & suspected cases

Nigeria
-------
Kaduna governmentt confirms there's a suspected case of Ebola at ABU.
2 Sep 2014: (PT) The Kaduna state government has confirmed that there is indeed a suspected case of Ebola virus disease in the state. ...
Premium Times had reported that a 19 year old law student at the Ahmadu Bello University was suspected to be down with the deadly Ebola virus in Kaduna and was on admission at the Ahmadu Bello University Teaching Hospital, (ABUTH). As indicated in the report, Bilyaminu Umar, spokesperson for ABUTH, confirmed the development. But no sooner than our report was published, the spokesperson to the minister, Mr Nwomeh, took to the social media to say the story was false. "The Kaduna report is totally untrue," Mr Nwomeh tweeted.

But the [Kaduna] state commissioner of health, Dr Thot Dogo, has now confirmed the development to Premium Times. Mr Dogo said in a telephone interview: "That case is a case of a student who took ill; we are just suspecting the ebolavirus. So, we have taken his blood sample for test. ... The patient is on isolation in Zaria. By tomorrow [3 Sep 2014] in the afternoon, the result will be ready from Lagos. We have already gone there after the ABUTH authorities alerted us, and our rapid response team took the blood sample. He has been at the hospital for about a week now. It's only fever. But I think he developed rashes with redness of the eyes. So, we are just taking precautions. ..."
https://www.premiumtimesng.com/news/167679-kaduna-govt-confirms-theres-suspected-case-of-ebola-at-abu.html#sthash.S1cjQoYt.dpuf

[See map of Nigeria's states, with Kaduna in yellow in the centre, at http://www.nigeriahc.org.uk/images/nigeria_map_m.gif. - Mod.JW]


St Lucia (Caribbean)
--------------
1 Sep 2014: (SNO ) Ebola medical team activated at Hewanorra International.
The Ministry of Health has activated an EVD medical team at the Hewanorra International Airport. ... Reports are that the officials at the airport were planning a protest on Sat [30 Aug 2014] since there was no medical team in place to deal with an international flight that had African nationals who could be possible EVD victims. ...
http://www.stlucianewsonline.com/ebola-medical-team-activated-at-hewanorra-international/#sthash.DvfoxQER.dpuf


Canada
------
2 Sep 2014: (St Catharines Standard) There is only a remote possibility a patient in quarantine at the Niagara Health System's St Catharines Hospital [Ontario] was infected by the deadly ebolavirus, but doctors are taking no chances. The NHS has released few details about the patient -- including the person's gender, age, city of residence or nationality -- who was placed in isolation on Mon [1 Sep 2014]. The patient went to the St Catharines emergency department with flu-like symptoms after having recently traveled from the heart of the EVD outbreak in West Africa. The NHS declined to say which West African nation the person had visited. The outbreaks are in Guinea, Liberia, Sierra Leone and Nigeria.
http://www.stcatharinesstandard.ca/2014/09/02/ebola-scare-in-st-catharines

