[6] Central African Republic: ebolavirus found in wildlife
Date: 2 Sep 2014
Source: Star Africa [machine trans. edited]
http://fr.starafrica.com/actualites/le-directeur-de-linstitut-pasteur-de-bangui-explique-les-raisons-de-labsence-debola-en-rca.html [in French]


"The ebolavirus is circulating in Central African wildlife, but conditions are perhaps not met for an epidemic to arise in the Central African Republic, the director of the Pasteur Institute of Bangui, Emmanuel Nakoune Yandoko, said on Mon 1 Sep 2014. "We captured animals such as rats, bats, monkeys and sibissi [giant cane rats, a national delicacy]. We sought ebolavirus, and we found it in the spleens of these animals," said Emmanuel Nakoune. ...

